Compare Pandoc highlight styles

I-Hsuan Lin

University of Manchester

March 05, 2021

Introduction

The Pandoc syntax highlighting changed in version 2.11 when showing R Markdown. Below I show viewers comparisons before and after version 2.11.

Supported styles

pandoc --list-highlight-styles
## pygments
## tango
## espresso
## zenburn
## kate
## monochrome
## breezedark
## haddock

Example code

pandoc -v | head -n 2
# The easiest way to get ggplot2 is to install the whole tidyverse:
install.packages("tidyverse")

# Alternatively, install just ggplot2:
install.packages("ggplot2")

# Or the development version from GitHub:
devtools::install_github("tidyverse/ggplot2")

library(ggplot2)

ggplot(mpg, aes(displ, hwy, colour = class)) +
        geom_point(size = 3, alpha = 1/10)
